# Generated code and benchmark artifacts. Everything here is reproducible by
# running `bench/run_bench.sh` (which also runs the `go run .` generator), so it
# is kept out of version control. The hand-written sources -- bench/*/data.go,
# bench/*/input.json, the scripts, main.go and pkg/support -- remain tracked.

# Lightning-generated unmarshalers (`// Code generated by the lightning generator ... DO NOT EDIT`)
*_unmarshal.go

# Benchmark harness written by bench/run_bench.sh (`// Code generated ... DO NOT EDIT`)
bench/*/bench_test.go

# easyjson sub-packages: the copied struct and the easyjson output are both generated
bench/*/ej/

# Benchmark output (machine-specific timings; regenerated each run)
bench/results.txt

# The large-json input is the ~8 MB SF citylots GeoJSON, too big to commit;
# run_bench.sh downloads it from the committed bench/large-json/input.url when
# absent. (Other cases' input.json files are small and stay tracked.)
bench/large-json/input.json

# Compiled generator binary, if `go build .` is ever run without -o /dev/null
/lightning

# Compiled Go test binaries (`go test -c`), e.g. the ones the A/B bench harness
# builds into bench/ — never artifacts to commit.
*.test
